            case: "Ashington Piggeries Ltd v Christopher Hill Ltd [1972] AC 441",
            principle: "The consumer guarantee (or implied condition in older Sale of Goods Acts) that goods correspond with their description relates to the identity of the goods, not necessarily their quality or fitness for purpose, unless the description itself also implies quality or fitness. If goods match the description given, even if defective in quality, there may not be a breach of this specific guarantee.",
            principle_zh: "消费者保证（或旧《货物销售法》中的默示条件）商品与其描述相符，这关系到商品的同一性，而不必然是其质量或对特定用途的适用性，除非描述本身也暗示了质量或适用性。如果商品与所给描述相符，即使质量有缺陷，也可能不构成对这一特定保证的违反。",
            summary: "Ashington Piggeries contracted with Christopher Hill for compounded animal feed made to a specified formula for mink. An ingredient (herring meal), supplied by a third party to Christopher Hill, was contaminated and toxic to mink, causing many deaths. Ashington Piggeries sued. The House of Lords held that while the feed was defective and unfit for purpose, it still corresponded with its description (compounded mink feed according to formula). The issue of description was about identity, not quality. (Other grounds for liability like fitness for purpose were relevant).",
            summary_zh: "阿欣顿养猪场与克里斯托弗·希尔公司签订合同，要求后者按照特定配方为其生产水貂复合饲料。其中一种由第三方供应给克里斯托弗·希尔公司的成分（鲱鱼粉）受到污染，对水貂有毒，导致大量水貂死亡。阿欣顿养猪场提起诉讼。上议院认为，虽然该饲料存在缺陷且不适合其用途，但它仍然符合其描述（根据配方生产的水貂复合饲料）。描述问题关乎同一性，而非质量。（其他责任基础如对特定用途的适用性则相关）。",
            scaffold: "Ashington Piggeries Ltd v Christopher Hill Ltd clarifies that the guarantee of correspondence with description focuses on whether the goods are what they are described as being, distinct from issues of their quality or fitness for a particular purpose, which are covered by other guarantees.",
            scaffold_zh: "阿欣顿养猪场有限公司诉克里斯托弗·希尔有限公司案阐明，与描述相符的保证侧重于货物是否如其所述，这与货物的质量或对特定用途的适用性问题不同，后者由其他保证涵盖。",
            statute: "Sale of Goods Act (context); ACL s 56 (Guarantee relating to the supply of goods by description)",
            statute_zh: "《货物销售法》（背景）；《澳大利亚消费者法》第56条（关于凭描述供应货物的保证）",
