            summary: "West parked his car in a council-operated car park and received a ticket with an exclusion clause stating the council was not responsible for loss or damage. The ticket also said it must be presented to take delivery of the vehicle. A thief, claiming to have lost his ticket, tricked an attendant into issuing a duplicate and was allowed to drive West's car away. West sued the council. The High Court held the council liable. The act of releasing the car to an unauthorised person without proper presentation of the ticket was outside the scope of the contract (not a mere negligent performance within it), so the exclusion clause did not protect the council.",
            summary_zh: "韦斯特将其汽车停放在市议会经营的停车场，并收到一张印有免责条款的票据，声明市议会对车辆损失或损坏概不负责。票据上还注明，取车时必须出示此票。一名小偷声称丢失了票据，欺骗服务员补发了一张，并获准将韦斯特的汽车开走。韦斯特起诉了市议会。高等法院裁定市议会应承担责任。在未适当出示票据的情况下将汽车交给未经授权的人，这一行为超出了合同范围（并非合同范围内的单纯过失履行），因此免责条款不能保护市议会。",
