            case: "Ermogenous v Greek Orthodox Community of SA Inc (2002) 209 CLR 95",
            principle: "The High Court cautioned against relying too heavily on rigid presumptions (e.g., that religious or non-commercial arrangements lack intention). The primary approach is to objectively assess all available evidence to determine whether the parties intended to create legal relations. The nature of the relationship (e.g., spiritual) does not automatically preclude a contract.",
