            summary: "Codelfa contracted with the State Rail Authority (SRA) to excavate tunnels, assuming it could work three shifts a day. Injunctions by local residents restricted work to two shifts, significantly increasing Codelfa's costs. Codelfa argued for an implied term that if its work method was disrupted, SRA would indemnify it for extra costs. The High Court refused to imply such a term, stating it was not obvious both parties would have agreed to it had they considered the possibility of injunctions. The contract was ultimately found to be frustrated.",
            summary_zh: "Codelfa与州铁路局（SRA）签订合同挖掘隧道，原以为每天可以三班倒工作。但当地居民申请的禁令将工作限制为两班倒，大大增加了Codelfa的成本。Codelfa主张合同中存在一项默示条款，即如果其工作方法受到干扰，SRA将赔偿其额外费用。高等法院拒绝默示此类条款，称如果双方当时考虑到禁令的可能性，并非显而易见双方都会同意该条款。合同最终被认定为落空。",
