            principle_zh: "个别董事单独行事时，通常不具有在与第三方签订合同（特别是在日常业务范围之外的重大交易中）时约束公司的习惯授权。公司由董事会集体管理。如果公司对外宣称某位个别董事拥有此类授权，则可能产生表见授权。",
            summary: "A director and a person purporting to be the company secretary of Northside Developments executed a mortgage over the company's main asset to secure a loan from Barclays Bank to a company controlled by that director (and not Northside). Northside received no benefit. The other directors of Northside were unaware. When Northside defaulted on other obligations, the issue of the mortgage's validity arose. The High Court held the mortgage was unenforceable against Northside because the director acting alone (even with the purported secretary) did not have actual or apparent authority to enter into such a substantial transaction that was not for Northside's benefit. The bank was put on inquiry.",
            summary_zh: "Northside Developments公司的一名董事和一名自称公司秘书的人签署了一份抵押合同，将公司的主要资产抵押，为该董事控制的另一家公司（而非Northside）从巴克莱银行获得的贷款提供担保。Northside并未从中受益。Northside的其他董事对此并不知情。当Northside未能履行其他义务时，该抵押合同的有效性问题浮出水面。高等法院裁定该抵押合同对Northside不具强制执行力，因为单独行事的董事（即使与所谓的秘书一起）没有实际或表见授权来签订如此重大的、并非为了Northside利益的交易。银行应进行查询。",
