            principle: "A mere inquiry or request for clarification of the terms of an offer does not constitute a counter-offer and does not terminate the original offer. The original offer remains open and capable of acceptance after such an inquiry.",
            principle_zh: "仅仅询问或要求澄清要约条款不构成反要约，也不会终止原要约。在此类询问后，原要约仍然有效并可被接受。",
            summary: "McLean offered to sell iron to Stevenson, Jacques & Co. at a certain price, offer open until Monday. On Monday morning, Stevenson telegraphed McLean asking if he would accept payment over two months, or if not, the longest limit he would give. McLean did not reply and later sold the iron to someone else. Before McLean's sale, Stevenson telegraphed acceptance of the original offer. The court held Stevenson's first telegram was a mere inquiry about terms, not a counter-offer. Thus, the original offer was still open when Stevenson accepted it, forming a binding contract.",
            summary_zh: "麦克莱恩提出以特定价格向史蒂文森·雅克公司出售铁，要约有效期至周一。周一上午，史蒂文森电告麦克莱恩，询问是否接受两个月内付款，或者如果不接受，最长付款期限是多少。麦克莱恩未回复，随后将铁出售给他人。在麦克莱恩出售之前，史蒂文森电告接受原要约。法院认为，史蒂文森的第一封电报仅仅是对条款的询问，而非反要约。因此，当史蒂文森接受时，原要约仍然有效，构成了有约束力的合同。",
            scaffold: "Stevenson, Jacques & Co. v McLean distinguishes a mere request for information, which keeps the original offer alive, from a counter-offer, which rejects it.",
            scaffold_zh: "史蒂文森·雅克公司诉麦克莱恩案区分了单纯的信息询问（使原要约继续有效）和反要约（拒绝原要约）。",
            statute: "Common Law of Contract",
            statute_zh: "合同普通法",
