            case: "Metropolitan Fire Systems Pty Ltd v Miller (1997) 23 ACSR 699",
            principle: "A company is insolvent if it is unable to pay all its debts as and when they become due and payable (cash flow test), not merely if its liabilities exceed its assets (balance sheet test). When assessing insolvency for the purpose of a director's duty to prevent insolvent trading, all of the company's resources, including credit resources and the timing of receivables and payables, must be considered.",
            principle_zh: "如果一家公司无法在其所有债务到期应付时偿还（现金流量测试），则该公司即为资不抵债，而不仅仅是其负债超过资产（资产负债表测试）。在为董事防止资不抵债交易的义务而评估破产时，必须考虑公司的所有资源，包括信贷资源以及应收和应付款项的时间安排。",
            summary: "Metropolitan Fire Systems had substantial overdue debts to creditors, some of whom were taking or threatening legal action. While it had some assets, most were not immediately realizable. The Federal Court held the company was insolvent. In determining insolvency, the court emphasized the cash flow test: whether the company could pay its debts as they fell due. Factors like the company's inability to pay current debts, overdue accounts, and lack of readily available funds or credit pointed to insolvency, even if assets theoretically exceeded liabilities.",
            summary_zh: "Metropolitan Fire Systems公司拖欠债权人大量逾期债务，部分债权人正在或威胁采取法律行动。虽然该公司拥有一些资产，但大部分无法立即变现。联邦法院裁定该公司资不抵债。在确定破产时，法院强调现金流量测试：即公司是否能够在其债务到期时偿还。诸如公司无力偿还当前债务、账户逾期以及缺乏随时可用的资金或信贷等因素均指向破产，即使理论上资产超过负债。",
            scaffold: "Metropolitan Fire Systems v Miller applied the cash flow test for insolvency, crucial for determining if directors breached their duty to prevent insolvent trading under the Corporations Act.",
            scaffold_zh: "Metropolitan Fire Systems 诉 Miller 案适用了破产的现金流量测试，这对于根据《公司法》确定董事是否违反了防止资不抵债交易的义务至关重要。",
            statute: "Corporations Act 2001 (Cth) (e.g., s 95A definition of solvency; s 588G duty to prevent insolvent trading)",
            statute_zh: "《2001年公司法（联邦）》（例如，第95A条偿付能力定义；第588G条防止资不抵债交易的义务）",
