            case: "Powell v Lee (1908) 99 LT 284",
            principle: "Acceptance of an offer must be communicated to the offeror by the offeree or by someone with the offeree's authority. Communication of acceptance by an unauthorized third party is not effective.",
            principle_zh: "要约的承诺必须由受要约人或其授权的人传达给要约人。未经授权的第三方传达承诺是无效的。",
            summary: "Powell applied for a headmaster position. The school managers (the offeree) decided to appoint him but did not formally communicate this decision to him. However, one of the managers, acting without authority, informed Powell that he had been appointed. Later, the managers rescinded their decision and appointed someone else. Powell sued for breach of contract. The court held there was no contract because the acceptance of his offer (his application) had not been officially communicated to him by someone with authority from the board of managers.",
            summary_zh: "鲍威尔申请了校长职位。学校管理委员会（受要约人）决定任命他，但未正式将此决定通知他。然而，其中一位管理人员在未经授权的情况下通知鲍威尔他已被任命。随后，管理委员会撤销了他们的决定并任命了其他人。鲍威尔以违约为由提起诉讼。法院认为不存在合同，因为对其要约（其申请）的承诺未经管理委员会有授权的人正式传达给他。",
