            principle: "A director may improperly use their position (contrary to s 182 of the Corporations Act or its predecessors) even if they subjectively believe they are acting in the best interests of the company and do not intend to act dishonestly. The test for 'improper use' involves an objective assessment of the director's conduct.",
            principle_zh: "即使董事主观上认为其行为符合公司的最佳利益且无意不诚实地行事，其仍可能不正当地使用其职位（违反《公司法》第182条或其前身规定）。“不正当使用”的测试涉及对董事行为的客观评估。",
            summary: "Chew, a director, caused companies he controlled to enter into transactions that ultimately benefited him or his associates, arguably to the detriment of those companies or their creditors. Even if Chew believed his actions were for the company's benefit, the High Court considered whether his use of position was objectively improper. The case established that 'impropriety' does not depend on consciousness of wrongdoing; it is an objective question based on the standards expected of a director.",
            summary_zh: "董事周先生使其控制的公司进行了一些交易，这些交易最终使他本人或其关联方受益，但可以说损害了这些公司或其债权人的利益。即使周先生认为其行为是为了公司的利益，高等法院仍审议了其使用职位是否客观上不正当。该案确立了“不正当性”不取决于对不当行为的认知；这是一个基于对董事预期标准的客观问题。",
