            principle: "A manufacturer of products owes a duty of care to the ultimate consumer to take reasonable care in the preparation of the products to ensure they are free from defects likely to cause injury to health, even if there is no contractual relationship between them. This established the 'neighbour principle': you must take reasonable care to avoid acts or omissions which you can reasonably foresee would be likely to injure your neighbour (persons so closely and directly affected by your act).",
            principle_zh: "产品制造商对最终消费者负有注意义务，应在产品制备过程中采取合理谨慎，以确保产品没有可能导致健康损害的缺陷，即使他们之间没有合同关系。这确立了“邻人原则”：您必须采取合理谨慎以避免那些您可以合理预见可能会伤害您的邻人（那些因您的行为而受到如此密切和直接影响的人）的行为或不作为。",
            summary: "Mrs. Donoghue's friend bought her a bottle of ginger beer manufactured by Stevenson. The bottle was opaque. After drinking some, a decomposed snail emerged from the bottle when the remainder was poured. Mrs. Donoghue suffered shock and gastroenteritis and sued the manufacturer. The House of Lords held (by majority) that Stevenson owed a duty of care to Mrs. Donoghue as the ultimate consumer, despite no contract between them, to ensure the product was free from harmful defects. This landmark case established the modern tort of negligence.",
            summary_zh: "多诺霍夫人的朋友为她购买了一瓶由史蒂文森制造的姜汁啤酒。瓶子是不透明的。喝了一些之后，当倒出剩余部分时，一只腐烂的蜗牛从瓶中出现。多诺霍夫人遭受了惊吓和肠胃炎，并起诉了制造商。上议院（以多数票）裁定，尽管多诺霍夫人与史蒂文森之间没有合同关系，史蒂文森作为最终消费者对其负有注意义务，以确保产品没有有害缺陷。这一里程碑式的案件确立了现代过失侵权法。",
