    case: "Hong Kong Fir Shipping Co. v Kawasaki Kisen Kaisha Ltd [1962]; Koompahtoo Local Aboriginal Land Council v Sanpine Pty Ltd (2007)",
    principle: "An intermediate or innominate term is one that is capable of being breached in various ways, some serious and some minor. The right to terminate depends on the gravity and consequences of the breach, not just the classification of the term itself.",
    principle_zh: "中间条款或无名条款是指可能以多种方式被违反的条款，有些违约行为严重，有些则轻微。终止合同的权利取决于违约的严重性和后果，而不仅仅是条款本身的分类。",
    summary: "If the breach of an intermediate term deprives the innocent party of substantially the whole benefit of the contract, they may terminate and claim damages. If the breach is minor, they can only claim damages. This approach provides more flexibility than the rigid condition/warranty distinction.",
    summary_zh: "如果违反中间条款使无过错方实质上丧失了合同的全部利益，他们可以终止合同并要求赔偿损失。如果违约行为轻微，他们只能要求赔偿损失。这种方法比僵化的条件/保证区分提供了更大的灵活性。",
    scaffold: "The term regarding [performance of the term] might be an intermediate term. The breach by [Party A] resulted in [describe consequences]. Given the severity of these consequences, the breach likely [does/does not] deprive [Party B] of substantially the whole benefit of the contract, meaning termination [is/is not] justified.",
    scaffold_zh: "关于[履行该条款]的条款可能是中间条款。[当事人A]的违约行为导致了[描述后果]。鉴于这些后果的严重性，该违约行为很可能[剥夺了/未剥夺][当事人B]合同的实质全部利益，这意味着终止合同[是/不是]合理的。",
