    summary: "A primary example is the Australian Consumer Law (ACL), which implies various consumer guarantees into contracts for the supply of goods and services to consumers (e.g., acceptable quality, fitness for purpose). State Sale of Goods Acts also imply terms into contracts for the sale of goods (though these can often be excluded, unlike many ACL guarantees).",
