    concept_zh: "免责条款 - 一般原则与通知",
    case: "Thornton v Shoe Lane Parking; Olley v Marlborough Court",
    principle: "An exclusion clause (or exemption clause) aims to limit or exclude one party's liability for breach of contract or negligence. For it to be effective, reasonable notice of the term must be given to the other party before or at the time the contract is made.",
