    summary: "If notice is given after the contract is formed, the clause is generally ineffective. The type of document is also relevant: if a document (e.g., a docket or ticket) is not one that a reasonable person would expect to contain contractual terms, specific attention must be drawn to the clause (Causer v Browne).",
    summary_zh: "如果在合同成立后才发出通知，则该条款通常无效。文件的类型也很重要：如果文件（例如票据或凭单）并非理性人会预期包含合同条款的文件，则必须特别提请注意该条款（Causer v Browne案）。",
