    case: "Causer v Browne [1952] VLR 1",
    principle: "An exclusion clause printed on a document that a reasonable person would not consider to be contractual (e.g., a mere receipt or voucher for collection) will generally not be incorporated as a term of the contract unless sufficient steps were taken to bring the clause to the recipient's attention as a contractual term.",
    principle_zh: "如果免责条款印在一份理性人不会认为是合同性质的文件上（例如，仅仅是收款凭证或领取凭单），则该条款通常不会被纳入合同条款，除非已采取足够措施提请接收方注意该条款为合同条款。",
    summary: "In Causer v Browne, a dry cleaning docket contained an exclusion clause. The court held it was ineffective because the customer would reasonably assume the docket was merely a voucher to collect the dress, not a document containing contractual terms. No sufficient notice of the clause as a term was given.",
    summary_zh: "在Causer v Browne案中，一张干洗票据包含免责条款。法院认为该条款无效，因为顾客会合理地认为该票据仅仅是领取衣物的凭证，而非包含合同条款的文件。未曾充分通知该条款为合同的一部分。",
