    summary: "In White v John Warwick, an exclusion clause stated 'Nothing in this agreement shall render the owners liable for any personal injuries'. The court held this was ambiguous as to whether it excluded liability in contract only, or also in tort (negligence). Applying contra proferentem, it was interpreted narrowly to exclude only contractual liability, not liability for negligence.",
    summary_zh: "在White v John Warwick案中，一项免责条款规定“本协议中的任何内容均不使所有者对任何人身伤害承担责任”。法院认为该条款对于其是仅排除合同责任，还是也排除侵权（过失）责任存有歧义。适用不利于起草方解释规则，该条款被狭义解释为仅排除合同责任，而不排除过失责任。",
