    case: "",
    principle: "A person is a 'consumer' under ACL s 3 if: (a) the amount paid/payable for goods/services did not exceed the prescribed amount (currently $100,000, previously $40,000); OR (b) the goods/services were of a kind ordinarily acquired for personal, domestic or household use or consumption; OR (c) the goods consisted of a vehicle or trailer acquired for use principally in the transport of goods on public roads.",
    principle_zh: "根据《澳大利亚消费者法》第3条，如果满足以下任一条件，则该人即为“消费者”：(a) 为商品/服务支付/应付的金额未超过规定金额（目前为100,000澳元，此前为40,000澳元）；或 (b) 该商品/服务属于通常为个人、家庭或家居使用或消费而获取的种类；或 (c) 该商品为主要用于在公共道路上运输货物的车辆或拖车。",
