    summary: "This crossing does not restrict the transferability of the cheque but removes full negotiability. It acts as a 'danger signal' (Permewan Wright case), warning that the cheque may have a defective title. The drawee financial institution must pay it into an account, not over the counter (s 54).",
    summary_zh: "这种划线不限制支票的可转让性，但取消了其完全流通性。它起到“危险信号”的作用（Permewan Wright案），警示该支票可能存在权利瑕疵。付款金融机构必须将其存入账户，不得柜台兑现（第54条）。",
    scaffold: "The cheque was crossed 'not negotiable'. This means that [Transferee] could not obtain a better title than [Transferor] had (Cheques Act s 55). If [Transferor]'s title was defective, then [Transferee]'s title is also defective because...",
