    summary: "Elements: Carrying on a business (repetitive/regular activity), in common (mutual agency and rights), with a view of profit. Advantages: Easy to form, pooling of resources/expertise, tax advantages (income split). Disadvantages: Unlimited liability for all partners, number usually limited (e.g., to 20, with professional exceptions), lack of permanence, potential for disputes. Limited Partnerships exist providing limited liability for some partners.",
