    case: "Baumgartner v Baumgartner (1987) (for constructive trusts)",
    principle: "A trust is an equitable obligation binding a person (the trustee) to deal with property over which they have control (the trust property) for the benefit of other persons (the beneficiaries). The trustee holds legal title, while beneficiaries hold equitable title.",
    principle_zh: "信托是一种衡平法上的义务，约束一个人（受托人）为他人（受益人）的利益处理其控制的财产（信托财产）。受托人拥有法定所有权，而受益人拥有衡平法上的所有权。",
    summary: "Key elements: Settlor (creates the trust), Trustee (administers the trust, owes fiduciary duties), Beneficiary (benefits from the trust), Trust Property, and Trust Instrument (deed). Trusts can be Express (intentionally created) or Non-Express (e.g., Implied, Constructive). Advantages: asset protection, tax effectiveness, family wealth management, limited liability if trustee is a company. Disadvantages: complex to establish and maintain, high costs, strict duties on trustees.",
    summary_zh: "关键要素：设立人（设立信托），受托人（管理信托，负有信托责任），受益人（从信托中受益），信托财产，以及信托文件（契约）。信托可以是明示信托（有意设立）或非明示信托（例如，默示信托、推定信托）。优点：资产保护，税务有效性，家族财富管理，如果受托人是公司则承担有限责任。缺点：设立和维持复杂，成本高，受托人责任严格。",
    scaffold: "The arrangement involving [property] being held by [Trustee] for the benefit of [Beneficiary] suggests a trust structure. This imposes fiduciary duties on [Trustee] to manage the property in the best interests of [Beneficiary].",
    scaffold_zh: "涉及由[受托人]为[受益人]的利益持有[财产]的安排表明这是一种信托结构。这赋予[受托人]信托责任，以[受益人]的最佳利益管理财产。",
    statute: "Common Law / Equity; State/Territory Trustee Acts (e.g., Trustee Act 1925 (NSW))",
    statute_zh: "普通法/衡平法；州/地区《受托人法》（例如《1925年受托人法（新南威尔士州）》）"
