    principle_zh: "《公司法》第181(1)条要求董事或其他高级职员在行使其权力并履行其职责时：(a) 出于善意，为公司的最佳利益；以及 (b) 为正当目的。",
    summary: "This duty is fiduciary. 'Good faith' requires directors to act honestly. 'Best interests of the corporation' generally means the interests of shareholders as a collective group, but may include creditors' interests when the company is insolvent or nearing insolvency (Walker v Wimbourne). 'Proper purpose' means powers must be exercised for the purpose for which they were conferred, not for a collateral or improper purpose.",
