    principle: "Section 588G of the Corporations Act imposes a duty on directors to prevent a company from incurring a debt if the company is insolvent at that time, or becomes insolvent by incurring that debt (or other debts at that time), AND there are reasonable grounds for suspecting insolvency.",
    principle_zh: "《公司法》第588G条规定，如果公司在发生债务时已资不抵债，或因发生该债务（或当时发生的其他债务）而资不抵债，并且有合理理由怀疑其资不抵债，则董事有义务防止公司发生该债务。",
    summary: "A director contravenes this section if they fail to prevent the company from incurring the debt and were aware of reasonable grounds for suspecting insolvency, or a reasonable person in a like position would have been so aware. 'Insolvency' is determined by the cash flow test (s 95A) - ability to pay debts as and when they fall due (Metropolitan Fire Systems). Breach can lead to civil penalties, compensation orders, and criminal charges if dishonesty is involved.",
    summary_zh: "如果董事未能阻止公司发生债务，并且他们知道有合理理由怀疑公司资不抵债，或者处于类似职位的理性人本应如此知晓，则董事违反此条规定。“资不抵债”由现金流量测试确定（第95A条）——即按期偿还到期债务的能力（Metropolitan Fire Systems案）。违规行为可能导致民事处罚、赔偿令，如果涉及不诚实行为，还可能导致刑事指控。",
    scaffold: "Under s 588G, a director has a duty to prevent insolvent trading. Here, when [Company] incurred the debt to [Creditor], were there reasonable grounds to suspect insolvency? Did [Director] fail to prevent this? This requires assessing [Company]'s ability to pay debts as they fell due.",
