    summary: "Liquidation can be voluntary (initiated by members if solvent, or creditors if insolvent) or compulsory (by court order, usually due to insolvency - s 95A). A liquidator is appointed to manage the process. Key aims: orderly realisation of assets, equitable distribution to creditors, investigation of company affairs.",
