    concept_zh: "遵循先例原则 (Stare Decisis)",
    case: "",
    principle: "The doctrine of precedent (stare decisis - 'to stand by things decided') requires courts to follow the legal principles established in previous decisions of higher courts within the same judicial hierarchy when deciding cases with similar facts.",
    principle_zh: "遵循先例原则（stare decisis - “恪守已决之事”）要求法院在审理具有相似事实的案件时，遵循同一司法等级体系中上级法院先前判决所确立的法律原则。",
    summary: "This ensures consistency, predictability, and fairness in the application of law. Key aspects include: binding precedents (from superior courts in the same hierarchy must be followed) and persuasive precedents (from other hierarchies or lower/same level courts, may be considered). The ratio decidendi of a case is binding, while obiter dicta are only persuasive.",
    summary_zh: "这确保了法律适用的一致性、可预测性和公平性。关键方面包括：有约束力的先例（必须遵循同一等级体系中上级法院的先例）和有说服力的先例（来自其他等级体系或下级/同级法院的先例，可予以考虑）。案件的判决理由具有约束力，而附带意见仅具有说服力。",
